author: Byron Hood
message:
DEVPROD-15875: Add Optibot configuration file for AI code review (#8838)

This adds a configuration file that is used by Optibot, an AI-powered code reviewer, to decide how to operate.

I disabled auto-summarization of a PR because we already tend to do that ourselves and have a clear template for it. This can be turned on later if we get lazy. But I enabled auto-review so that we can see how well it performs.

If we don't like the quality of the code reviews, change "reviews.auto" to false and that should turn it off.

Auto-approvals are also off. I think that would make it accept a PR if it doesn't find issues. That seems premature at this point.

author: Dylan Richardson
message:
DEVPROD-12040: Add conditional writes to s3.put (#8464)

This commit updates s3.put to support S3's new conditional writes
feature. The conditional writes feature guarantees that a write will not
succeed if the remote key already exists. This check respects s3's
strong read-after-write data model. This change removes our existing code
that did a get before the put (which could race) with the S3-native API
for ensuring conditional writes. Bucket owners may also now apply bucket
policies which require that this parameter is used.

In order to enable this feature, I updated to the latest version of pail.
